The paper deals with finding pure Nash equilibria in graphical games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm proposed uses both classical computation and quantum annealing, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and quantum computing (cs.CC). The problem of finding pure Nash equilibria can also be formulated as a combinatorial optimization problem, which could place the paper under the categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and optimization (cs.SI).
